## Changelog

---

### 2026-03-20 · `Garmin_clean.json`

#### Added
- Native Garmin workout integration — fetches planned workouts via `/workouts` and `/workout-detail`, including name, duration and step-by-step instructions
- Multi-model fallback in Groq AI Analysis — tries `openai/gpt-oss-120b` first, falls back to `llama-3.3-70b-versatile` with exponential backoff (15s / 30s / 60s / 90s)
- 30-day weight trend graph in the HTML report

#### Improved
- Training advice now based on live Garmin Connect workouts instead of a fixed internal schema
- Today's step count tracked separately from the 10-day rolling average

#### Removed
- "Fetch 5K Schedule" node and the hardcoded 8-week training schema
- Workflow reduced from 8 to 7 nodes

---

### 2026-03-19 · `server.py`

#### Added
- `/workouts` — planned workouts from Garmin Connect (`?start=`, `?limit=`)
- `/workout-detail` — full step breakdown for a single workout (`?id=`)
- `/herverbind` POST — forces a fresh login without restarting the container
- `@requires_client` decorator — unified error handler across all endpoints (`503` / `401` / `502`)
- Structured logging via Python `logging` — replaces bare `print()` statements

#### Improved
- `/health` — now returns display name and today's date
- `/gewicht` — supports both single-day (`?datum=`) and date-range (`?start=` / `?eind=`)
- Authentication flow — token login and credential login fully separated
- MFA handling — rate limit (429) and wrong code (401/403) caught with specific error messages
- `vo2max` — date-range loop refactored into a `_fetch()` h
